    "headline": "Airbnb Debut Bond Sale Reshapes Debt Mix And Future Cash Flows",
    "summary": "Airbnb (NasdaqGS:ABNB) has launched its first investment grade bond offering, targeting $2.5b in long term, fixed rate debt. The deal comes as the company approaches the maturity of $2b in convertible notes and reshapes its capital structure. This move introduces recurring interest expense and has prompted a strong market reaction around the stock. Airbnb enters this bond sale with its shares at $126.3 and a mixed return profile, including a 5.2% decline over the past week and a 5.6% gain...",
